[[File:Canta LX.jpg|thumb|Canta LX]] The '''Canta''' is a two-seat [[microcar]] from the Netherlands specifically created for [[disability|disabled]] drivers.<ref name="trouw2006">{{cite news|first=Hans |last=van Vinkeveen |url=http://www.trouw.nl/tr/nl/4324/Nieuws/article/detail/1479059/2006/11/17/Met-een-Canta-kun-je-over-de-stoep-rijden-en-je-mag-hem-overal-parkeren.dhtml |title=Met een Canta kun je over de stoep rijden en je mag hem overal parkeren. |language=nl |publisher=Trouw.nl |date=2006-11-17 |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref> It was developed in 1995 by [[Waaijenberg]] together with the [[Delft University of Technology]]. In addition to the standard petrol-engined production models, an electric Canta was designed for the German market but it has remained at the prototype stage. In the Netherlands, it is classified as a [[mobility aid]] because the width of the vehicle is only 1.10 metres, thus it may - unlike larger microcars - be used on [[cycle path]]s as well as sidewalks and footpaths; in addition a [[driver's license]] is not required.<ref name="trouw2006"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rijksoverheid.nl/onderwerpen/bijzondere-voertuigen/vraag-en-antwoord/wat-zijn-de-verkeersregels-voor-een-gehandicaptenvoertuig-met-een-motor.html |title=Wat zijn de verkeersregels voor een gehandicaptenvoertuig met een motor? &#124; Vraag en antwoord |publisher=Rijksoverheid.nl |language=nl |date= |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref>
Each Canta is built with the adaptations required by the customer, such as locating controls and switches on the left or right side, or all on the steering wheel. Seats have a wide range of adjustment and can [[Swivel seat|swivel]] to ease entry and exit. Instead of having a driver's seat, the "Ride-in Canta" ({{lang|nl|Inrij Canta}}) model is designed so that a [[wheelchair]] user can enter by a ramp at the rear and drive while seated in their wheelchair.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amsterdamlogue.com/the-worlds-smallest-car.html |title=The world’s smallest car? Meet the “Canta” &#124; Amsterdam Travel Guide |publisher=Amsterdamlogue.com |date=2008-06-08 |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref> The rear of the vehicle is lowered to the ground when parked and is raised pneumatically when the engine is started.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.waaijenberg.com/canta/de-inrij-canta |title=De Inrij Canta: De ideale oplossing voor rolstoelgebruikers &#124; Waaijenberg Mobiliteit |publisher=Waaijenberg.com |language=nl |date=2014-01-25 |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gnJ-QCchaqk |title=Rolstoel canta, Wheelchair canta Waaijenberg |publisher=YouTube |date=2008-06-06 |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref>
== ''De Canta danst!'' == ''De Canta danst!'' is a TV co-production by Viewpoint Productions and NTR in cooperation with the [[Dutch National Ballet]] that choreographically features the microcar.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nederland.tv/nederland-2/de-canta-danst.html |title=Over Ons |publisher=Nederland.TV |language=nl |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref> It is part of ''Het Nationale Canta ballet'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hetnationalecantaballet.nl/ |title=het nationale CANTA ballet |publisher=Hetnationalecantaballet.nl |language=nl |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref> which in turn is an initiative of writer [[Karin Spaink]], radio producer Bert Kommerij and actress-director [[Maartje Nevejan]]. It was choreographed by [[Ernst Meisner]] of the Dutch National Ballet, with the music written by composer [[Robin Rimbaud]]. The project was financially supported by Stichting Doen and the SNS REAAL Fund. The performances took place on 28 June 2012 at the Westergasfabriek.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.westergasfabriek.nl/whats-on/nieuws/het-nationale-canta-ballet |title=Bijzondere eenmalige voorstelling van het Nationale Canta Ballet &#124; Westergasfabriek |publisher=Westergasfabriek.nl |language=nl |date=2012-05-16 |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref>
