{{Orphan|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox company | name = RAVPower | logo = RAVPower_logo.jpg | industry = [[Consumer Electronics]] | type = Private | foundation = 2011 | homepage = [http://www.ravpower.com/ www.ravpower.com] | hq_location = [[San Jose, California]], United States }}
'''RAVPower''' is an American consumer electronics brand founded in 2011 and owned by Sunvalleytek, which is a branch of the [http://www.sunvalley.com.cn/about.html Chinese owned Sunvalley Group]. The company's current product line is primarily focused on [[battery charger]]s, including portable powerbanks and solar chargers, shifting away from its previous focus on laptop and cell phone batteries. RAVPower products are sold through its own website and the [[Amazon Marketplace]].
== Products ==
=== Portable Powerbanks === On December 18, 2015, RAVPower launched its Turbo+ 20100 mAh External Battery, the world's first portable [[Powerback|powerbank]] to include both Qualcomm Quick Charge 3.0 technology and a [[USB-C]] port.<ref>{{cite web|title=RAVPower's Turbo+ 20100 mAh External Battery Brings Fastest Charging Time for Mobile Devices|url=http://www.einnews.com/pr_news/309952663/ravpower-s-turbo-20100-mah-external-battery-brings-fastest-charging-time-for-mobile-devices|work=EIN News|accessdate=4 February 2016}}</ref>
== Technology ==
=== iSmart === Patented by RAVPower, products with iSmart technology automatically detect the optimal charging current for connected devices and adjust to their power needs.<ref>{{cite web|title=RAVPower Dual-Port, 4-Port + 6-Port USB Wall Chargers deliver fast, quality power at crazy low prices|url=http://9to5mac.com/2014/12/15/review-ravpower-dual-4-6-port-usb-wall-chargers/|work=9to5M|accessdate=15 December 2014}}</ref> This allows for faster and smarter charging for smartphones and tablets, including the Apple iPhone and iPad.<ref>{{cite web|title=BGR|url=http://bgr.com/2016/01/04/portable-smartphone-charger-sale-amazon-3/|accessdate=4 January 2016}}</ref>
